events.name: Brighton & Hove Albion at Nottingham Forest

headlines.description: Brazilian forward Danilo scored his first goal for Nottingham Forest to help seal a 3-1 Premier League victory over Europe-chasing Brighton.
headlines.shortLinkText: Forest out of relegation zone with Brighton win

headlines.description: Brentford condemned Chelsea to their fifth defeat in five games under interim coach Frank Lampard on Wednesday with a 2-0 win at Stamford Bridge.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chelsea slump to 5th straight loss under Lampard

headlines.description: A bullet header from Joel Matip gave Liverpool a 2-1 Premier League win over West Ham United that moves them above Tottenham Hotspur in the table.
headlines.shortLinkText: Liverpool win to keep European hopes alive

headlines.description: Kevin De Bruyne scored twice as Manchester City took a giant step toward retaining the Premier League title with a dominant 4-1 win over Arsenal.
headlines.shortLinkText: City humble Arsenal to take charge of title race
